    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Inspection</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="0">
            <title>Cylinder Head Bolt Reusability Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A head bolt thread gauge is needed for the successful completion of this procedure.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Spin the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_108.xml" xrefid="t2650505">head bolt thread gauge</hotlnk>
                    onto the cylinder head bolt across the entire length of threads.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the thread gauge encounters any resistance on the threads, the bolt is considered
                    stretched beyond limits and therefore cannot be resused.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard and replace any cylinder head bolt that fails the reusability test with new
                    cylinder head bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
